[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: France win show jumping team gold

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
France's show jumpers won Olympic gold in the equestrian team event at the Rio Games.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The French quartet of Philippe Rozier, Kevin Staut, Roger Yves Bost and Penelope Leprevost gave France their second equestrian title in Rio after team success in eventing.
The United States were second and Germany third after they beat Canada in a jump-off for bronze.
Defending champions Great Britain failed to reach the final.
